commitResults.messageTitle: Add mapping add, list, delete command set

commitResults.messageBody:
Mapping is a separate data type of interest, and share a unique
structure compared to other data types, and require certain rules.

We will duplicate and extend on the current system to support
the new mapping data type.

This is done for consistency with the existing system, and just
overall reliability.

Refer to LocalCourse for a similar example.

commitResults.messageTitle: Update course delete to block when mapped
commitResults.messageBody:
A mapping requires data fields from LocalCourse
and PartnerCourse, and thus these dependencies
cannot be deleted.

Let's block deletion of such courses if they
exist in a mapping.

This ensures that integrity of data, and to
prevent accidental deletions.

commitResults.messageTitle: Add model support for mapping search command
commitResults.messageBody:
Mapping search feature is one of the core features.
We need to ensure it is programmed well.

We have separate classes for the predicates, which
allows us to define the fine details of logic.

It allows us to make use of defensive programming.

commitResults.messageTitle: Add error mesasge for absent arguments
commitResults.messageBody:
Users need to know that all arguments must be present.

Let's use the existing empty argument detection, and
simply trigger an error message upon detection.

Capitalising on an existing function is the simplest
and most effective way to improve the product.
